00:35:11.860 --> 00:35:15.400
to information, so we can
check different stories

00:35:15.400 --> 00:35:18.100
and bring our own truth.

00:35:18.100 --> 00:35:19.910
But also, everybody
has an opinion,

00:35:19.910 --> 00:35:24.640
so even anybody can do a YouTube
video and explain dumb stuff

00:35:24.640 --> 00:35:26.110
and have a follow-up.

00:35:26.110 --> 00:35:28.690
So my question is,
what worries you

00:35:28.690 --> 00:35:30.880
and what do you think
will be a solution on top

00:35:30.880 --> 00:35:32.501
of better education, et cetera?

00:35:32.501 --> 00:35:34.792
Could you say it worries you
that we live in this world

00:35:34.792 --> 00:35:35.292
right now?

00:35:43.215 --> 00:35:44.840
ANTOINE BELLO: From
the top of my head,

00:35:44.840 --> 00:35:48.920
intolerance is the one thing
that worries me the most.

00:35:48.920 --> 00:35:57.110
It's the reason why I commit
so much for Wikipedia.

00:35:57.110 --> 00:36:02.080
I've been a strong supporter
of Wikipedia for years now.

00:36:02.080 --> 00:36:06.520
I think they do an excellent
job and a very important job

00:36:06.520 --> 00:36:10.780
at disseminating information,
and disseminating information

00:36:10.780 --> 00:36:15.620
that has managed to
build a consensus.

00:36:15.620 --> 00:36:18.790
And that, to me, is
absolutely crucial.

00:36:18.790 --> 00:36:23.560
And it's not a coincidence if
Wikipedia is banned in China,

00:36:23.560 --> 00:36:29.680
is banned in Turkey, was
sometimes banned in France.

00:36:29.680 --> 00:36:31.060
Would you believe it?

00:36:31.060 --> 00:36:34.160
Certain articles were
blocked in France,

00:36:34.160 --> 00:36:36.139
which is no longer possible.

00:36:36.139 --> 00:36:37.930
Wikipedia has changed
the way they operate.

00:36:37.930 --> 00:36:41.350
Now you have to ban
the entire site.

00:36:41.350 --> 00:36:45.370
You cannot ban only a
selected few articles.

00:36:45.370 --> 00:36:51.250
So intolerance
obviously scares me.

00:36:51.250 --> 00:36:54.550
And intolerance, I think--

00:36:54.550 --> 00:36:57.160
what scares me is
people, what they

00:36:57.160 --> 00:37:02.530
call the useful idiots or the
people who think they know,

00:37:02.530 --> 00:37:05.260
they think they are
in control, and they

00:37:05.260 --> 00:37:08.730
should be the one admitting that
they know very, very little.

00:37:08.730 --> 00:37:11.920
Citizens who don't inform
themselves, for instance,

00:37:11.920 --> 00:37:13.100
who don't do their job.

00:37:13.100 --> 00:37:14.560
I think citizen is a job.

00:37:14.560 --> 00:37:15.910
Citizen is not a right.

00:37:15.910 --> 00:37:18.220
Well, it is obviously
a right, but it

00:37:18.220 --> 00:37:21.610
comes with duties
and responsibilities.

00:37:21.610 --> 00:37:24.580
Going to vote without
doing your homework, to me,

00:37:24.580 --> 00:37:28.480
is a betrayal of
the democratic pact,

00:37:28.480 --> 00:37:31.150
and it is a betrayal
that many, many people

00:37:31.150 --> 00:37:33.580
are guilty of today.

00:37:33.580 --> 00:37:36.310
So that worries me.

00:37:43.480 --> 00:37:47.560
AUDIENCE: First of all, I never
realized that storytelling

00:37:47.560 --> 00:37:50.110
was so pervasive.

00:37:50.110 --> 00:37:52.090
Maybe a lot of you
are similar to me,

00:37:52.090 --> 00:37:55.690
but I have a longtime
friend that we've

00:37:55.690 --> 00:38:01.060
known for several years and
who consistently tells stories.

00:38:03.970 --> 00:38:07.540
We've stuck with him
throughout-- a lot

00:38:07.540 --> 00:38:09.940
of people, when they meet
him, they kind of find

00:38:09.940 --> 00:38:12.210
it kind of comical.

00:38:12.210 --> 00:38:15.220
We call it giving
him an 80% discount,

00:38:15.220 --> 00:38:18.400
because we know that
probably his story started

00:38:18.400 --> 00:38:23.170
with a fact somewhere, but then
he added 80% to 90% of a story

00:38:23.170 --> 00:38:25.840
on top of it.

00:38:25.840 --> 00:38:28.780
My question is, because
we have discussions

00:38:28.780 --> 00:38:34.570
amongst friends about, should
we try to intervene and get him

00:38:34.570 --> 00:38:35.860
some help?

00:38:35.860 --> 00:38:39.100
Because it affects
his personal life.

00:38:39.100 --> 00:38:43.510
Most people are not attracted
to a person where they obviously

00:38:43.510 --> 00:38:51.550
are telling stories that are
obvious stories all the time.

00:38:51.550 --> 00:38:53.560
Or should we just leave
it, because his ego

00:38:53.560 --> 00:38:55.440
is now all caught up.

00:38:55.440 --> 00:38:57.160
He believes his own
stories, of course,

00:38:57.160 --> 00:39:00.490
so his ego is all
caught up in the stories

00:39:00.490 --> 00:39:04.870
that he's fabricated on this
fictional life, essentially.

00:39:04.870 --> 00:39:05.935
So it's a complex issue.

00:39:05.935 --> 00:39:07.310
I just wanted to
see if you had--

00:39:07.310 --> 00:39:08.800
ANTOINE BELLO: How old is he?

00:39:08.800 --> 00:39:11.590
AUDIENCE: He's in his mid 40s.

00:39:11.590 --> 00:39:14.980
ANTOINE BELLO: My last book,
the one that some of you

00:39:14.980 --> 00:39:17.620
have in front of them,
[SPEAKING FRENCH],,

00:39:17.620 --> 00:39:21.430
is about a pathological
impostor and his relationship

00:39:21.430 --> 00:39:25.030
with his psychiatrist, and
the way this relationship

00:39:25.030 --> 00:39:29.380
develops over the years,
over the decades, even.

00:39:29.380 --> 00:39:33.940
I've documented myself
quite a bit for that book.

